  "prompt": "What if Obama dies before Trump is inaugurated? Would Joe Biden assume presidency or Trump take oath earlier than planned?",
  "response": "If Barack Obama were to die before Donald Trump's inauguration, the Presidential Succession Act of 1947 would come into play. According to this law, if the President dies, resigns, or is removed from office, the Vice President would assume the presidency. At the time, Joe Biden was the Vice President under President Obama.\n\nTherefore, if Obama had died before Trump's inauguration, Joe Biden would have become the President of the United States until the scheduled inauguration date of Donald Trump on January 20, 2017. Trump would not take the oath of office earlier than planned; he would still be inaugurated on the designated date as per the Constitution.\n\nIn summary, Joe Biden would have served as President for the remaining days of Obama's term, and then Donald Trump would be sworn in as planned on January 20, 2017.",
